                            <comment id="12884844" author="streamy" created="Fri, 2 Jul 2010 22:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So then we do not want to go through with other split changes that have regions re-open on server hosting parent?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12884846" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 2 Jul 2010 22:57:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IMO this issue is a workaround for the master&apos;s inability to balance on requests load (instead of regions). With better load balancing, we should do a better job at redistributing regions on the cluster so this patch won&apos;t be needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12884864" author="stack" created="Sat, 3 Jul 2010 00:02:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To be clear this issue is inthe main targeted at 0. 20 branch to help out our Mozilla brethren&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12887949" author="stack" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2010 19:38:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 0.20 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
